[b]Chandelier Flip Radar [WavesUnchained][/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
ATR-based trailing stop that ratchets with price and flips between long and short mode when the close crosses the opposing stop level. The long stop only ever moves up and the short stop only ever moves down — the level never pulls back against the prevailing trend. On top of the binary flip, a five-level state system makes trend weakening visible before the actual direction change: bars fade, turn yellow (warning zone), and turn orange (danger zone) as price approaches the flip trigger.

[b]Key improvements over standard implementations[/b]
[list]
[*]The inactive stop is shown as a gray line — you see at a glance how far price must move to flip direction
[*]Warning/danger distance is measured to the real flip trigger (previous stop value), not the current stop
[*]A body filter gates the actual direction change: doji and inside-bar flips are ignored, not just unlabeled
[/list]

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*]Ratchet mechanism: active stop only moves in the trend direction, never against it
[*]Extremum mode: close-based (default, smoother) or wick-based (more responsive)
[*]Five-level state: strong / softening / warning (yellow) / danger (orange), per direction
[*]Bull/bear trap markers: wick crossed the flip trigger intrabar but the close held — often a stop hunt or liquidity grab
[*]Three adaptive multiplier modes: Off (fixed), Simple (volatility-regime scaling), AI (K-means clustering self-selects the best-performing factor)
[*]AI cluster selector (Best / Average / Worst) and adaptive performance-weighted AMA stop line
[*]Optional bar coloring by state, background fill, buy/sell labels at direction changes
[/list]

[b]Calculation[/b]
[list]
[*]Long stop = highest(close, period) − ATR × multiplier, ratcheted up only
[*]Short stop = lowest(close, period) + ATR × multiplier, ratcheted down only
[*]Direction flips to long when close > previous short stop; to short when close < previous long stop — only when the candle body passes the body filter
[/list]

[b]Alerts[/b]
Five named alert conditions: direction change, buy, sell, bull trap, bear trap. Also fires through a single "any alert() call" setup — on confirmed bars by default.

